If you want to optimize the `scatter_variance` function and get the correct variance for each index, you'll need to first compute the sums and sums of squares separately for each unique index. Then, use that information to calculate the variance per index. We also want to perform these operations efficiently.

Here are some optimizations that can be done:

1. Use `std::vector<double>` to store the sum and sum of squares to preserve precision.
2. Allocate memory for the vectors before the operations to prevent reallocations during push-backs.
3. Compute each index's mean first, then use it to compute the variance in a second pass.
4. Accumulate the sums and sums of squares in one loop instead of two separate loops.
5. Use the single-pass algorithm for variance computation to improve numerical stability.

Here's the optimized code:

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
#include <unordered_map>
#include <cmath>

template <typename T>
std::vector<double> scatter_variance(const std::vector<T>& src, const std::vector<int>& index, size_t dim_size) {
    if (src.empty()) {
        return std::vector<double>(dim_size, 0.0);
    }

    // Using an unordered map to accumulate the sums and counts.
    std::unordered_map<int, std::pair<double, size_t>> acc_map;

    // Accumulating the sums and counts for each index.
    for (size_t i = 0; i < src.size(); ++i) {
        auto& acc = acc_map[index[i]];
        acc.first += src[i];  // Sum of elements
        acc.second += 1;      // Count of elements
    }

    // Calculating mean for each index and preparing for variance computation.
    std::vector<double> means(dim_size, 0.0);
    for (const auto& pair : acc_map) {
        means[pair.first] = pair.second.first / pair.second.second;
    }

    // Variance computation.
    std::vector<double> variances(dim_size, 0.0);
    for (size_t i = 0; i < src.size(); ++i) {
        double diff = src[i] - means[index[i]];
        variances[index[i]] += diff * diff;
    }

    // Finalize the variance by dividing by count.
    for (auto& pair : acc_map) {
        variances[pair.first] /= pair.second.second;
    }

    return variances;
}

int main() {
    std::vector<double> src = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};
    std::vector<int> index = {0, 0, 1, 1, 1};
    size_t dim_size = 2;

